left to right direction
hide empty description
state "Observe" as observe
state "EvaluateReady" as evaluate_ready
state "Ready" as ready
state "Retryable" as retryable
state "Failed" as failed
observe : read spec, tracked status, delete intent,\nand current OCI lifecycle
state "ResolveByLookup" as resolve_by_lookup
state "RejectUnsupportedDrift" as reject_unsupported_drift
[*] --> observe : reconcile
observe --> resolve_by_lookup : tracked identity missing
resolve_by_lookup --> evaluate_ready : lookup or create reaches\nACTIVE
resolve_by_lookup --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
observe --> evaluate_ready : OCI state in ACTIVE
observe --> failed : unresolved OCI error or non-success state
evaluate_ready --> reject_unsupported_drift : force-new or conflicting\ndrift detected
reject_unsupported_drift --> ready : wait for spec or live state change
evaluate_ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
ready --> ready : no supported drift remains
retryable --> retryable : OCI remains retryable
failed --> failed : OCI remains terminal
note right of ready
shared diagram:
shared/diagrams/shared-controller-state-machine.svg
Start from the shared controller phase model and
specialize imported provider states, delete
targets, and failure exits here.
archetype batch: Generated service-manager
controllers map provider states into the shared
controller phases with explicit finalizer and
requeue policies.
service: osubsubscription
slug: subscription
kind: Subscription
archetype: generated-service-manager
status/finalizer: required / none
requeue: updating
provider states: create none; update none;
delete none
supported drift: none
reject before mutate: force-new fields
compartment_id, plan_number, subscription_id,
buyer_email (+5 more)
create-only fields: none
list lookup: oci_osubsubscription_subscriptions
filters compartment_id, plan_number,
subscription_id, buyer_email
conflicts: none
open gaps: bind-versus-create,
lifecycle-classification
OSubscription exposes ListSubscriptions only in
the pinned SDK, so the published runtime is
query-backed and observe-only.
Reconcile requires compartmentId plus exactly
one of planNumber, subscriptionId, or
buyerEmail. The runtime also passes
isCommitInfoRequired, sort controls,
xOneGatewaySubscriptionId, and xOneOriginRegion
when those spec fields are populated.
SubscriptionSummary does not expose a clean
top-level OCID or the request filter fields, so
the package-local read model echoes the selector
fields into projected list items and accepts
only a unique exact match.
No OCI create, update, get, or delete operation
is published. Kubernetes delete is local-only,
and the runtime leaves status.status.ocid empty.
A blank sdkStatus string is treated as retryable
updating. Any non-empty sdkStatus settles
success while the raw string remains visible on
the CR.
end note
